Usage: wlogout [options...]

   -h, --help                      Show help message and stop
   -l, --layout </path/to/layout>  Specify a layout file
   -v, --version                   Show version number and stop
   -C, --css </path/to/css>        Specify a css file
   -b, --buttons-per-row <0-x>     Set the number of buttons per row
   -c  --column-spacing <0-x>      Set space between buttons columns
   -r  --row-spacing <0-x>         Set space between buttons rows
   -m, --margin <0-x>              Set margin around buttons
   -L, --margin-left <0-x>         Set margin for left of buttons
   -R, --margin-right <0-x>        Set margin for right of buttons
   -T, --margin-top <0-x>          Set margin for top of buttons
   -B, --margin-bottom <0-x>       Set margin for bottom of buttons
   -p, --protocol <protocol>       Use layer-shell or xdg protocol
   -s, --show-binds                Show the keybinds on their corresponding button
   -n, --no-span                   Stops from spanning across multiple monitors
   -P, --primary-monitor <0-x>     Set the primary monitor

